# GSD plan execution (Cursor)

Global reference: `~/.cursor/references/gsd-plan-execution-cursor.md` · Personal skill: `~/.cursor/skills/gsd-plan-execution-cursor/`

When the user asks to execute a GSD plan (e.g. `.planning/phases/**/PLAN.md`, `/gsd:execute-phase`, or "execute plan with subagents"):

- **Do not** spawn the `gsd-executor` subagent type.
- **Do** spawn your own sub-agents via the Task tool — e.g. `generalPurpose`, `explore`, or `shell` — with a detailed prompt that includes the full task from the plan, workspace path, verification commands, and commit message if the plan specifies one.

Orchestrate waves yourself (sequential when tasks depend, parallel when independent). Collect results and verify before marking the plan done.

This preference applies in **Cursor** only; it overrides default GSD execute-phase guidance that routes work to `gsd-executor`.
